SIMPLE: rough
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rough
<hw>Rough</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Rougher</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Roughest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>rou<?/</ets>,
<ets>rou</ets>, <ets>row</ets>, <ets>rugh</ets>, <ets>ruh</ets>, AS.
<ets>r<?/h</ets>; akin to LG. <ets>rug</ets>, D. <ets>rug</ets>, D.
<ets>ruig</ets>, <ets>ruw</ets>, OHG. <ets>r<?/h</ets>, G.
<ets>rauh</ets>, <ets>rauch</ets>; cf. Lith. <ets>raukas</ets> wrinkle,
<ets>rukti</ets> to wrinkle. ⟦root⟧ 18. Cf. <er>Rug</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having inequalities, small ridges,
or points, on the surface; not smooth or plain; <as>as, a <ex>rough</ex>
board; a <ex>rough</ex> stone; <ex>rough</ex> cloth</as>.</def>
Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Not level; having a broken surface;
uneven; -- said of a piece of land, or of a road.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Rough,
uneven ways.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>Not polished; uncut; -- said of a gem; <as>as, a
<ex>rough</ex> diamond</as>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>Tossed in waves;
boisterous; high; -- said of a sea or other piece of water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>More unequal than the <qex>roughest</qex> sea.</q> <rj><qau>T.
Burnet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(d)</sd> <def>Marked by coarseness; shaggy; ragged; disordered;
-- said of dress, appearance, or the like; <as>as, a <ex>rough</ex>
coat</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A visage <xex>rough</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Dryden.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Rough</xex>satyrs.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Milton.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, figuratively, lacking refinement, gentleness,
or polish.</def> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Not
courteous or kind; harsh; rude; uncivil; <as>as, a <ex>rough</ex>
temper</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A fiend, a fury, pitiless and <qex>rough</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A surly boatman, <qex>rough</qex> as wayes or winds.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>Marked by severity or violence; harsh; hard;
<as>as, <ex>rough</ex> measures or actions</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On the <qex>rough</qex> edge of battle.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A quicker and <qex>rougher</qex> remedy.</q>
<rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Kind words prevent a good deal of that perverseness which
<qex>rough</qex> and imperious usage often produces.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(c)</sd> <def>Loud and hoarse; offensive to the ear; harsh;
grating; -- said of sound, voice, and the like; <as>as, a <ex>rough</ex>
tone; <ex>rough</ex> numbers</as>.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(d)</sd> <def>Austere; harsh to the taste; <as>as, <ex>rough</ex>
wine</as>.</def> <sd>(e)</sd> <def>Tempestuous; boisterous; stormy;
<as>as, <ex>rough</ex> weather; a <ex>rough</ex> day</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He stayeth his <qex>rough</qex> wind.</q> <rj><qau>Isa. xxvii.
8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Time and the hour runs through the <qex>roughest</qex> day.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(f)</sd> <def>Hastily or carelessly done; wanting finish;
incomplete; <as>as, a <ex>rough</ex> estimate; a <ex>rough</ex>
draught</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<cs><p><col><b>Rough diamond</b></col>, <cd>an uncut diamond; hence,
colloquially, a person of intrinsic worth under a rude exterior.</cd><--
= diamond in the rough --> -- <col><b>Rough and ready</b></col>.
<sd>(a)</sd> <cd>Acting with offhand promptness and efficiency</cd>.
⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>rough and ready</xex> understanding.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>Produced offhand.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Some <xex>rough and
ready</xex> theory.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Tylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></cs>

<p><ent>Rough</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rough
<hw>Rough</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Boisterous weather.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Fletcher.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rude fellow; a coarse bully; a rowdy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>In the rough</b></col>, <cd>in an unwrought or rude
condition; unpolished; <as>as, a diamond or a sketch <ex>in the
rough</ex></as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Contemplating the people <qex>in the rough</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rough</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Rough
<hw>Rough</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a rough manner; rudely;
roughly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sleeping <qex>rough</qex> on the trenches, and dying stubbornly in
their boats.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rough</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Rough
<hw>Rough</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To render rough; to
roughen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To break in, as a horse, especially for military
purposes.</def> <rj><au>Crabb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To cut or make in a hasty, rough manner; -- with
<xex>out</xex>; <as>as, to <ex>rough</ex> out a carving, a
sketch</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Roughing rolls</b></col>, <cd>rolls for reducing, in a
rough manner, a bloom of iron to bars.</cd> -- <col><b>To rough
it</b></col>, <cd>to endure hard conditions of living; to live without
ordinary comforts.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roughcast</ent>⟦br⟧
